# kube-context-allowlist.example
#
# Temporary per-session bypass. If a command contains any substring listed here,
# the guard allows it unconditionally. One token per line; '#' starts a comment.
#
# Resolution order (first existing file wins):
#   1. $OPENCODE_KUBE_GUARD_ALLOWLIST
#   2. ~/.claude/.kube-context-allowlist
#   3. this bundled example
#
# Example:
#   echo 'my-unique-command-marker' >> ~/.claude/.kube-context-allowlist
